  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">South Sudan: Increasing Access to Justice for Juveniles</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1) To improve access to justice for juveniles in South Sudan by strengthening the relevant competencies of civil society, social workers and paralegals working with juveniles, and facilitating long-term pre-conditions to foster the quality and capacity of justice delivery.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Indirect: South Sudan public</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims to enhance access to justice for juveniles by strengthening the capacity of civil society organizations (CSOs), paralegal organizations, law firms and social workers in the area of legal aid pro-bono service and assistance, reducing the arbitrary, unlawful and prolonged detention of juveniles at police cells and long-remand detention at the prisons, improving case disposal rates, and improving juvenile detention conditions.</narrative>
  </description>
